s Step 1.";i:12;s:69:"Some doors will be supplied with two springs and some will have four.";i:13;s:44:"Assemble springs with sheaves on the ï¬‚oor.";i:14;s:55:"A 38 x 1-14 bolt and nut are used to attach the sheave.";i:15;s:52:"If your door was supplied with four large extension.";i:16;s:172:"To do this you will need to first detach one end of the spring from its mounting point at the back of the garage door rail farthest point away from the garage door opening.";i:17;s:196:"Then detach the lift cable from its connection point on the door rail near the garage door just above the garage opening and thread the loose cable around the sheave pulley attached to the spring.";i:18;s:52:"HOW TO CHOOSE A NEW EXTENSION SPRING AND INSTALL IT.";i:19;s:46:"Garage door extension springs are color-coded.";i:20;s:100:"This allows you to go to the hardware store and pick out the replacement springs in about 5 minutes.";i:21;s:79:"As you can see in the picture below the last coil on my spring was painted red.";i:22;s:51:"So I chose the new spring that had this color code.";i:23;s:159:"Watch our how-to videos to learn more about measuring and replacing your garage door extension springs and call us at 1-866-813-7899 if you have any questions.";i:24;s:25:"05 0 Reviews Part Finder.";i:25;s:79:"1 Extension springs are color coated see the chart below and order accordingly.";i:26;s:17:"2 Weigh the door.";i:27;s:144:"For a single car door place a bath scale in the center of the opening remove all spring tension from the door and lower the door onto the scale.";i:28;s:52:"Hook the spring onto a lower hole and test the door.";i:29;s:81:"Hook the spring one more hole lower or higher until the door is closing properly.";i:30;s:31:"Change the length of the cable.";i:31;s:112:"The following instructions demonstrate how to replace extension springs on a one-piece single panel garage door.";i:32;s:40:"On this garage door there was no opener.";i:33;s:95:"If you have an opener you will need to disengage the opener and unplug the power to the opener.";i:34;s:67:"How to Install a Garage Door New garage door installation overview.";i:35;s:67:"An older double garage door can weigh anywhere from 250 to 450 lbs.";i:36;s:21:"Two types of springs.";i:37;s:98:"Release the tension on side-mounted extension springs by lifting the door and locking it in place.";i:38;s:20:"Buying a steel door.";i:39;s:78:"If you had a hook or a bracket you should have been able to leave it in place.";i:40;s:62:"Have your partner hold the spring in its approximate location.";i:41;s:95:"There is a loop on the end of the cable that hooks to the pin on the bottom of the garage door.";i:42;s:78:"The cable next goes to the pulley that is attached to the bracket on the wall.";i:43;s:100:"Replacing garage door extension springs is not a difficult task provided you know all the key steps.";i:44;s:136:"Granted garage door spring installation work requires time and attention so it is best to save the task for the afternoon of a free day.";i:45;s:127:"If done carefully you should be able to balance garage door extension springs in their place and get the door to work like new.";i:46;s:108:"Garage door extension springs counterbalance the weight of garage doors to make them easy to open and close.";i:47;s:56:"Extension springs are stretched with cables and pulleys.";i:48;s:56:"One end of the cable attaches to the bottom of the door.";i:49;s:91:"The other end of the cable is usually secured to the horizontal track angle with an s-hook.";i:50;s:73:"Completely open your garage door and unplug the power cord to the opener.";i:51;s:75:"Place a C-clamp on each track underneath the the bottom garage door roller.";i:52;s:76:"This will prevent the door from rolling down to the ground in the next step.";i:53;s:81:"For extra protection you can put a step ladder underneath the center of the door.";i:54;s:225:"The springs install with an S-Hook to the stationary brackets that hang the horizontal tracks from the ceiling while the other end of the spring is connected to a pulley and safety cable assembly installed on the garage door.";i:55;s:95:"As the torsion springs close the door extension springs extend lightening the load of the door.";i:56;s:49:"For extension springs this is in the up position.";i:57;s:69:"To keep the door from falling it must be clamped to hold it in place.";i:58;s:50:"Raise the door and release the garage door opener.";i:59;s:73:"Push the door up as far as you can to release the tension on the springs.";i:60;s:27:"Use two pair of vice grips.";i:61;s:161:"- Extension springs doors must never be operated without a properly installed spring containment cable and installed according to the manufacturers instructions.";i:62;s:175:"Garage Door Extension Springs At Star Door Parts all of our replacement garage door extension springs are coated for extended life and are rated for a minimum of 10000 cycles.";}}